                    <!-- Introduction -->
                    <div class="mb-6">
                        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-2">Introduction (5 minutes)</h3>
                        <ul class="list-disc pl-6">
                            <li>Begin with a question: "What's something you want to achieve financially in the next 1-5 years?"</li>
                            <li>Discuss how vague goals ("save more money") are less effective than specific ones</li>
                            <li>Present statistics on goal achievement rates with and without written plans</li>
                            <li>Preview the learning objectives for the lesson</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    
                    <!-- Key Concepts -->
                    <div class="mb-6">
                        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-2">Key Concepts: SMART Framework (10 minutes)</h3>
                        <ul class="list-disc pl-6">
                            <li>Introduce each component of SMART goals:
                                <ul class="list-disc pl-6">
                                    <li>Specific: Precisely what will be accomplished</li>
                                    <li>Measurable: Quantifiable indicators of progress</li>
                                    <li>Achievable: Realistic given resources and constraints</li>
                                    <li>Relevant: Aligned with broader values and objectives</li>
                                    <li>Time-bound: Clear deadline or timeframe</li>
                                </ul>
                            </li>
                            <li>For each component, provide financial examples and non-examples</li>
                            <li>Use visual aids to reinforce each concept</li>
                            <li>Address common misconceptions about goal difficulty and specificity</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    
                    <!-- Short-term vs. Long-term Goals -->
                    <div class="mb-6">
                        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-2">Short-term vs. Long-term Goals (12 minutes)</h3>
                        <ul class="list-disc pl-6">
                            <li>Define timeframes for different goal categories:
                                <ul class="list-disc pl-6">
                                    <li>Short-term: 0-1 year</li>
                                    <li>Mid-term: 1-5 years</li>
                                    <li>Long-term: 5+ years</li>
                                </ul>
                            </li>
                            <li>Discuss the characteristics and challenges of each timeframe</li>
                            <li>Explain the importance of having goals in multiple timeframes</li>
                            <li>Present examples of financial goals in each category</li>
                            <li>Facilitate brief small group discussions on balancing different timeframes</li>
                            <li>Have students identify one goal they have in each timeframe</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    
                    <!-- Real-World Examples -->
                    <div class="mb-6">
                        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-2">Real-World Examples: Case Study Analysis (10 minutes)</h3>
                        <ul class="list-disc pl-6">
                            <li>Present contrasting case studies:
                                <ul class="list-disc pl-6">
                                    <li>Case 1: Vague, unmeasurable goals with no clear timeframe</li>
                                    <li>Case 2: SMART goals with clear action steps</li>
                                </ul>
                            </li>
                            <li>In small groups, have students:
                                <ul class="list-disc pl-6">
                                    <li>Identify strengths/weaknesses in each approach</li>
                                    <li>Revise the weak goals to make them SMART</li>
                                    <li>Predict outcomes for each person based on their approach</li>
                                </ul>
                            </li>
                            <li>Facilitate whole-class discussion on key insights</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    
                    <!-- Skill Builder Activity -->
                    <div class="mb-6">
                        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-2">Skill Builder Activity: SMART Goals Worksheet (13 minutes)</h3>
                        <ul class="list-disc pl-6">
                            <li>Introduce the SMART Goals Worksheet structure</li>
                            <li>Model completing one financial goal using the worksheet</li>
                            <li>Guide students in selecting their own financial goals to develop</li>
                            <li>Allow independent work time with teacher circulation</li>
                            <li>Provide prompts for students who struggle to identify goals</li>
                            <li>Check for completeness and alignment with SMART criteria</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    
                    <!-- Reflection & Wrap-up -->
                    <div class="mb-6">
                        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-2">Reflection & Wrap-up (5 minutes)</h3>
                        <ul class="list-disc pl-6">
                            <li>Facilitate a brief goal prioritization discussion</li>
                            <li>Have students identify their highest priority financial goal</li>
                            <li>Discuss challenges in maintaining focus on financial goals</li>
                            <li>Preview the Day 2 Learning Lab activities</li>
                            <li>Assign any pre-work needed for Day 2</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    
                    <!-- Discussion Prompts -->
                    <div class="mb-6">
                        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-2">Discussion Prompts</h2>
                        <ul class="list-disc pl-6">
                            <li><strong>For Introduction:</strong> "Why do you think people often fail to achieve their financial goals?" (Expected responses: goals too vague, lack of plan, unrealistic expectations, no accountability)</li>
                            <li><strong>For SMART Framework:</strong> "How might making a goal 'measurable' increase your chances of achieving it?" (Expected responses: provides clear success criteria, allows progress tracking, motivates through visible improvement)</li>
                            <li><strong>For Timeframe Discussion:</strong> "What are the challenges in balancing short-term wants with long-term financial goals?" (Expected responses: immediate gratification vs. delayed benefits, difficulty visualizing future needs, competing priorities)</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    
                    <!-- Differentiation Strategies -->
                    <h2 class="section-header text-xl">Differentiation Strategies</h2>
                    <div class="mb-6">
                        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-2">For Advanced Students</h3>
                        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-4">
                            <li>Encourage development of more complex, interconnected goal systems</li>
                            <li>Challenge them to create detailed action plans with contingencies</li>
                        </ul>
                        
                        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-2">For Struggling Students</h3>
                        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-4">
                            <li>Provide partially completed SMART goal examples</li>
                            <li>Focus on one timeframe initially</li>
                            <li>Offer structured templates with prompts</li>
                        </ul>
                        
                        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-2">For ELL Students</h3>
