                        <h4 class="font-medium text-gray-800 mb-1">Key Day 1 Concepts to Review:</h4>
                        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-2">
                            <li>SMART goal framework components</li>
                            <li>Differences between short, mid, and long-term goals</li>
                            <li>Characteristics of effective financial goals</li>
                        </ul>
                        
                        <h4 class="font-medium text-gray-800 mb-1">Podcast Discussion Points:</h4>
                        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-2">
                            <li>How SMART goals apply specifically to financial planning</li>
                            <li>Research on goal achievement factors</li>
                            <li>Common pitfalls in financial goal setting</li>
                        </ul>
                        
                        <h4 class="font-medium text-gray-800 mb-1">Learning Lab Introduction:</h4>
                        <ul class="list-disc pl-6">
                            <li>Frame today's activities as building on the basic SMART framework</li>
                            <li>Emphasize the importance of implementation planning</li>
                            <li>Explain that the end product will be a comprehensive goal achievement system</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    
                    <!-- Activity 1 -->
                    <div class="mb-6">
                        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-2">Activity 1: Goal Analysis Station (10 minutes)</h3>
                        <h4 class="font-medium text-gray-800 mb-1">Setup Instructions:</h4>
                        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-2">
                            <li>Provide Goal Analysis Station templates</li>
                            <li>Display examples of strong and weak goals for each SMART component</li>
                            <li>Arrange for individual work with teacher circulation</li>
                        </ul>
                        
                        <h4 class="font-medium text-gray-800 mb-1">Facilitation Steps:</h4>
                        <ol class="list-decimal pl-6 mb-2">
                            <li>Explain the component-by-component analysis process (2 minutes)</li>
                            <li>Guide students to evaluate their Day 1 goals against each SMART criterion (6 minutes)</li>
                            <li>Support students in refining weak elements (2 minutes)</li>
                        </ol>
                        
                        <h4 class="font-medium text-gray-800 mb-1">Key Teaching Points:</h4>
                        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-2">
                            <li>The importance of specificity in financial targets</li>
                            <li>How to determine if a goal is truly achievable</li>
                            <li>Creating meaningful measurement systems</li>
                            <li>Ensuring relevance to personal values and priorities</li>
                        </ul>
                        
                        <h4 class="font-medium text-gray-800 mb-1">Monitoring Guidance:</h4>
                        <ul class="list-disc pl-6">
                            <li>Check for honesty in self-assessment</li>
                            <li>Help students recognize vague language in their goals</li>
                            <li>Encourage realistic refinements to unachievable goals</li>
                            <li>Look for goals that may need complete restructuring</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    
                    <!-- Activity 2 -->
                    <div class="mb-6">
                        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-2">Activity 2: Financial Goal Timeline Builder (12 minutes)</h3>
                        <h4 class="font-medium text-gray-800 mb-1">Setup Instructions:</h4>
                        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-2">
                            <li>Students should access the Timeline Builder tool</li>
                            <li>Provide examples of well-structured timelines with milestones</li>
                            <li>Display reference information on typical financial goal timeframes</li>
                        </ul>
                        
                        <h4 class="font-medium text-gray-800 mb-1">Facilitation Steps:</h4>
                        <ol class="list-decimal pl-6 mb-2">
                            <li>Demonstrate the timeline builder with a sample goal (3 minutes)</li>
                            <li>Guide students in breaking down their goals into milestone steps (2 minutes)</li>
                            <li>Support students in setting realistic timeframes for each milestone (5 minutes)</li>
                            <li>Check for logical progression and appropriate pacing (2 minutes)</li>
                        </ol>
                        
                        <h4 class="font-medium text-gray-800 mb-1">Key Teaching Points:</h4>
                        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-2">
                            <li>The importance of breaking large goals into manageable steps</li>
                            <li>How to determine intermediate progress indicators</li>
                            <li>Creating milestone celebrations to maintain motivation</li>
                            <li>Aligning timeline with available resources and constraints</li>
                        </ul>
                        
                        <h4 class="font-medium text-gray-800 mb-1">Monitoring Guidance:</h4>
                        <ul class="list-disc pl-6">
                            <li>Check for appropriate sequencing of milestones</li>
                            <li>Help students develop specific actions for each milestone</li>
                            <li>Look for overly ambitious or unrealistic timelines to adjust</li>
                            <li>Encourage consideration of external factors (school schedule, etc.)</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    
                    <!-- Activity 3 -->
                    <div class="mb-6">
                        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-2">Activity 3: Obstacle Course Challenge (10 minutes)</h3>
                        <h4 class="font-medium text-gray-800 mb-1">Setup Instructions:</h4>
                        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-2">
                            <li>Provide Obstacle Course Challenge cards</li>
                            <li>Display common financial goal obstacles and example solutions</li>
                            <li>Arrange for small group collaboration</li>
                        </ul>
                        
                        <h4 class="font-medium text-gray-800 mb-1">Facilitation Steps:</h4>
                        <ol class="list-decimal pl-6 mb-2">
                            <li>Introduce the concept of proactive obstacle identification (2 minutes)</li>
                            <li>Guide students in identifying likely barriers to their goals (3 minutes)</li>
                            <li>Facilitate peer brainstorming for solutions (3 minutes)</li>
                            <li>Support students in selecting and documenting the best strategies (2 minutes)</li>
                        </ol>
                        
                        <h4 class="font-medium text-gray-800 mb-1">Key Teaching Points:</h4>
                        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-2">
                            <li>Common psychological barriers to financial goal achievement</li>
                            <li>External obstacles vs. internal obstacles</li>
                            <li>The importance of having multiple solution strategies</li>
                            <li>Developing resilience through obstacle planning</li>
                        </ul>
                        
                        <h4 class="font-medium text-gray-800 mb-1">Monitoring Guidance:</h4>
                        <ul class="list-disc pl-6">
                            <li>Ensure students identify both internal and external obstacles</li>
                            <li>Help students develop specific, actionable solutions</li>
                            <li>Encourage realistic assessment of obstacle difficulty</li>
                            <li>Look for opportunities to share effective strategies among students</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    
                    <!-- Activity 4 -->
